      "name": "Pressure-head curve validation against FDA experimental data",
      "description": "Simulated pressure-head values at 5 flow-speed combinations (3 L/min–5 L/min × 2500–3500 RPM) compared against FDA-published experimental measurements for the generic centrifugal pump. Mean absolute error 4.1%, maximum error 6.8%, all within the ±10% acceptance band. Turbulence model sensitivity study (k-ω SST vs. realizable k-ε) shows < 3% variation in pressure head.",
