      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation — 5-point operating map",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) computed via the Giersiepen power-law model integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks for 2000 seed particles per operating point. Predicted RH values at all 5 operating conditions are below 1.0 (range 0.61–0.93), consistent with the predicate device reference dataset. Worst-case operating point identified at 5 L/min / 3500 RPM (RH = 0.93).",
      "comparisonMetric": "RH < 1.0 at all 5 operating points",
      "passFailStatus": "Pass"
