      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical decision criterion and computed from validated flow-field quantities.",
      "rationale": "RH is computed from Lagrangian particle-track shear stress histories using the Giersiepen power-law model, which is the regulatory standard for computational hemolysis assessment. Pressure head and wall shear stress are validated surrogates that directly feed the hemolysis model. The acceptance criterion RH < 1.0 maps directly to the predicate device comparison required by the 510(k) pathway."
    },
